sku.fruugo_attribute_doc: Partner's item identifier, Fruugo includes this value in all communications regarding item information such as orders

productName.fruugo_attribute_doc: Title of the product to be displayed on the product details page. Brand + Category + Defining Quality + Item Name + Pack Count if applicable. Example: George Girls'  Short-Sleeve Polo; Hanes Men's V-Neck Tees, 3-Pack

longDescription.fruugo_attribute_doc: Complete description that will be displayed on the item page   as a bulleted list. Enter the item's key features, benefits, and other notables, each on its own line. Use HTML to create the headings, line breaks,  and bulleted list. Example: - Fabric content   - Features and/or attributes related to the product as a whole, such as pattern, fabric, etc.)  - Neckline  - Sleeves  - Fit  - Additional details (any info on tag)   - Hem details   - Bonus item/accessory, if applicable  - Care instructions

shelfDescription.fruugo_attribute_doc: Abbreviated list of key item features in no more than three bullet points.   This is viewable in search, category, and shelf pages. Format bullet points with HTML.   Example: - V-neck   - Studded details   - Loose fit

shortDescription.fruugo_attribute_doc: Overview of the key selling points of the item, marketing content, and highlights in paragraph form. For SEO purposes,  repeat the product name and relevant keywords here. HTML is supported,  and should be used only for making paragraph breaks. Plain text is also  acceptable; it will render as a single paragraph.   Example: The George - Girls" Short Sleeve Polo Shirt will make a great addition to your daughter"s  uniform wardrobe.  This short-sleeved girls" shirt has a flat knit collar and cuff for a comfortable fit. Plus, it"s tagless, so your daughter"s skin won"t be irritated by a scratchy tag. This girls" short sleeve polo is made from a cotton blend, and treated with Scotchgard for stain protection.  It has a two-button placket, an extended back hem and vents on each side hem. The girls" polo shirt is machine washable and very easy to maintain.

mainImage\/mainImageUrl.fruugo_attribute_doc: Location of the image. URLs must begin with http:// or https:// Example: http://www.fruugo.com/main_image.jpg

productIdentifiers\/productIdentifier\/p.fruugo_attribute_doc: Type of unique identifier used in the 'Product ID' field.Example: UPC; GTIN; ISBN; ISSN; EAN
Alphanumeric ID that uniquely identifies the product. Example: X12345

productTaxCode.fruugo_attribute_doc: Code used to identify tax properties of the product.

brand.fruugo_attribute_doc: If item does not have a brand, enter 'Unbranded' Example: HP; Toshiba; Unbranded

shippingWeight\/value.fruugo_attribute_doc: Please provide the value for the weight.

color\/colorValue.fruugo_attribute_doc: Color value as provided by the manufacturer. Example: Aqua; Burgundy; Mauve; Fuchsia

cellPhoneServiceProvider.fruugo_attribute_doc: The company responsible for the provision of the device's cellular service.      Example: ATT; Verizon

esrbRating.fruugo_attribute_doc: The rating as provided by the Entertainment Software Rating Board.   Example: Pending; Unrated; Early Childhood; Mature; Teen; Everyone 10+; Not Rated; Adults Only

alcoholContentByVolume.fruugo_attribute_doc: Percentage of alcohol by volume. Example: 40% Alcohol by Volume

foodForm.fruugo_attribute_doc: Describes the form of the food if the food is sold in a variety of forms,   such as sliced and unsliced, whole or halves, etc. Example: Frozen; Granules; Liquid; Bars; Fresh;Whole; Stewed; Sliced; Chopped; Diced; Blended

shoeCategory.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Baby Girl Shoes; Baby Boy Shoes; Toddler Girl Shoes; Toddler Boy Shoes; Girls' Shoes; Boys' Shoes; Women's Shoes; Men's Shoes

gender.fruugo_attribute_doc: To specify target gender of the item. Example: Women; Men; Girls; Boys; Unisex

mpaaRating.fruugo_attribute_doc: Motion Picture Association of America Rating  Example: G; PG; PG-13; R; NC-17; Not Rated

ageRange.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: 0-12 Months; 12-24 Months; 2-4 Years; 5-7 Years; 8-11 Years; 12 Years  Up; All Ages
ageRange.fruugo_attribute_enum: 0-12 Months,12-24 Months,2-4 Years,5-7 Years,8-11 Years,12  Up

isEnergyGuideLabelRequired.fruugo_attribute_doc: Denotes whether the label is required for the item. The FTC's   Appliance Labeling Rule requires retailers to display energy cost information for certain refrigerators,   freezers, furnaces, televisions, clothes washers, dishwashers, water heaters, pool heaters, and room air    conditioners. Example: Y; N

energyGuideLabel.fruugo_attribute_doc: Image URL of the energy guide label.     Example: http://fruugo.com/energy_guide_label.html

finish.fruugo_attribute_doc: Overall finish of the item.     Example: Natural; Unfinished; Brown; Espresso; Oak

homeDecorStyle.fruugo_attribute_doc: Describes home furnishings and decorations according to various themes,     styles, and tastes. Example: French; Vintage; Traditional; Contemporary; Rustic

powerType.fruugo_attribute_doc: Provides information on the exact type of power used by the item.     Example: Electric; Batteries

isRemoteControlIncluded.fruugo_attribute_doc: Is a remote control included with the item? Example: Y; N

seatingCapacity.fruugo_attribute_doc: The number of people that can be accommodated by the available seats of an item.     Example: 2; 4; 8

btu.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates British thermal units for heating and cooling appliances.     Example: 100000.0

ceeTier.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: CEE Tier I; Cee Tier III
ceeTier.fruugo_attribute_enum: CEE Tier I,CEE Tier II,CEE Tier III

tripLeverPlacement.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Front left of tank; Right side of tank

batteriesRequired.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates if batteries are required to use the item.     Batteries may or may not be included. To specify battery inclusion and type,      use the 'Has Batteries' and 'Battery Technology Type' attributes in the root spec. Example: Y; N

isPowered.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that an item is powered. Example: Y; N

subject.fruugo_attribute_doc: The 'aboutness' of an item, distinct from the genre.     It may be the subject of a documentary, nonfiction book, or art print.     Example: Art for Kids; Dance; Hobbies

form.fruugo_attribute_doc: Describes the way the item is dispensed or consumed,     including its texture or other physical characteristics.     Example: Spray; Foam; Cream; Gel; Tablet; Suppository

isPortable.fruugo_attribute_doc: Is the item portable? Example: Y; N

hasCfl.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates if any part of the item is or has a compact fluorescent light bulb.     Example: Y; N

isLightingFactsLabelRequired.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates if item requires lighting facts label. Example: Y; N

lightingFactsLabel.fruugo_attribute_doc: URL of the location of the label. URLs must begin with http:// or https://   Label must include brightness specified lumens, estimated energy cost per year, life, light appearance, scale,    energy used, and special handling information needed for disposal, as outlined by the FTC.    Example: http://www.example.com/lighting_label.html

isBareTool.fruugo_attribute_doc: A 'bare' tool is a battery powered item that does not come with a     battery or charger. Example: Y; N

numberOfLightBulbs.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates number of light bulbs in lamps and lighting items. Example: 1; 2

variantGroupId.fruugo_attribute_doc: Required if item is a variant. Make up a number for 'Variant Group ID,' and add this to all variations of the same product.    Partners must ensure uniqueness of their Variant Group IDs.

isPrimaryVariant.fruugo_attribute_doc: Note whether item is intended as the main variant in a variant grouping.     Example: Y; N

manufacturer.fruugo_attribute_doc: Manufacturer is the maker of the product.     This is the name of the company that produces the product, not necessarily the brand name of the item.

numberOfPieces.fruugo_attribute_doc: The total number of pieces included in the item's package. Example: 15; 325

cleaningCareAndMaintenance.fruugo_attribute_doc: Description of how the item should be cleaned and maintained.

isIndustrial.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that an item can be used in an industrial setting or has an industrial application. Example: Y; N

shape.fruugo_attribute_doc: Physical shape of the item. Example: Aviator; Cateye; Horned; Oval; Rectangle; Round; Square; Wayfarer

loadPosition.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates whether washing machines and dryers are top load or front load. Example: Top; Front

isSmart.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates whether a device is among the set of 'smart'   appliances (indicating Web, wireless, or interactive technology has been integrated   into device functionality). Example: Y; N

bedSize.fruugo_attribute_doc: Denotes the size of a bed, a bed's parts, mattress, or bed linens.   Example: Toddler; Twin; Twin XL; Full; Full XL; Queen; King; California King

rugSize.fruugo_attribute_doc: The approximate size of rugs and rug runners, measured in feet,     and and expressed as Length x Width (for example: a ten-foot-long by five-foot-wide rug's      measurements should be entered as 5 x 10). Example: Under 2' x 3'; 2.5' x 4.5'; 7' 5' x 10' 4' x 12' 3'

clockNumberType.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Arabic/Standard; Roman Numerals; No Numbers

curtainPanelStyle.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Tab Top; Grommet; Back Tab; Rod Pocket

scent.fruugo_attribute_doc: Descriptive term for fragrance. Example: Vanilla; Geranium; Rose

displayTechnology.fruugo_attribute_doc: The primary technology used for the item's display. Example: OLED; Retina Display; DLP; Plasma; LCD

collection.fruugo_attribute_doc: A collection is a particular group of items that have the same visual style,     made by the same brand.     Example: L'Oreal Infallible; Sophia;

modelNumber.fruugo_attribute_doc: Having this information allows customers to search for items on the site and   informs product matching.

manufacturerPartNumber.fruugo_attribute_doc: MPN uniquely identifies the product to its manufacturer.   For many products this will be identical to the model number.   Some manufacturers distinguish part number from model number.

isReusable.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates the item can be used more than once. Example: Y; N

isDisposable.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates the item is intended for single use. Example: Y; N

isAntique.fruugo_attribute_doc: Is an old collectable item Example: Y; N

isPersonalizable.fruugo_attribute_doc: Denotes if the item can be customized in some way, including engraved,   embroidered, stamped, etched, etc. Example: Y; N

isSet.fruugo_attribute_doc: Please indicate whether this product consists of two or more items sold together   as a set. (example: lipstick + lip-liner) Example: Y; N

isRetractable.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that the item can be withdrawn into a holder, as in a cord or leash.   Example: Y; N

isWheeled.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that an item has wheels and can be rolled. Example: Y; N

isFoldable.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that an item can be folded. Example: Y; N

isAssemblyRequired.fruugo_attribute_doc: Is product unassembled and must be put together before use?

assemblyInstructions.fruugo_attribute_doc: URL location showing assembly instructions for items requiring assembly.

isAdultProduct.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates if item is adult in nature and should not   appear in results for children's products. Example: Y; N

isRecyclable.fruugo_attribute_doc: Recycle is the act of processing used or abandoned materials     for use in creating new products or capable of being used again. Example: Y; N

isInflatable.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that an item can be inflated. Example: Y; N

isAnimated.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that a product has powered, moving parts. Example: Y; N

makesNoise.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that the item has a noise-making feature. Example: Y; N

clothingSizeType.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Regular; Slim; Plus; Petite Plus; Tall; Husky; Juniors; Big; Petite; Junior Plus; Big  Tall

apparelCategory.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Boys; Girls; Juniors; Maternity Plus; Maternity Wear; Men;     Men's Big  Tall; Petites; School Uniforms; Women; Women's Plus; Young Men's
apparelCategory.fruugo_attribute_enum: Young Men's,Maternity Plus,School Uniforms,Men's Big   Tall,Women's Plus,Petites,Maternity Wear,Newborn Girl,Boys,Baby Boy,Girls,Baby Girl,Newborn Boy,  Juniors,Women,Men

animalType.fruugo_attribute_doc: The common generic name for the type of animal.     Example: Dog; Cat; Bird; Hamster; Lizard; Frog; Fish; Horse

condition.fruugo_attribute_doc: For refurbished items; used for non-perishables     Example: New; Used; Refurbished

animalHealthConcern.fruugo_attribute_doc: Type of condition that the item is intended to address.     Example: Flea  Tick Control; Dental Care; Allergy Relief; Hairball Care

isDrugFactsLabelRequired.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates if item requires drug facts labeling. Example: Y; N

drugFactsLabel.fruugo_attribute_doc: URL of the location of the label. Example: http://www.example.com/drug_facts.html

instructions.fruugo_attribute_doc: Text of how to use the item.

isReflective.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that the item contains material that reflects light,     especially for nighttime safety. Example: Y; N

flavor.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Chicken  Lamb; Bacon; Beef  Liver; Tuna

petFoodForm.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Dry; Canned; Fresh; Flakes; Granules

isGrainFree.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates item is made without grain ingredients. Example: Y; N

feedingInstructions.fruugo_attribute_doc: Instructions for feeding food to the animal. Example: Feed 1/2 cup per 10 lbs.     weight. Puppies may need up to twice the amount as adult dogs.

ingredients.fruugo_attribute_doc: The list of ingredients contained in an item, according to FDA guidelines.     Example: Carbonated Water; Natural Flavors

animalBreed.fruugo_attribute_doc: The specific breed or species of animal. Example: German Shepherd; Goldfish;     European Spacefoot Toad

animalLifestage.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Puppy; Kitten; Adult; All Lifestages

childCarSeatType.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Convertible; Infant; Booster; Travel Systems

facingDirection.fruugo_attribute_doc: Which direction the car seat faces.     Example: Forward-Facing; Rear-Facing; Convertible

babyClothingSize.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Preemie; Newborn; One Size; 0-3 Months; 3-6 Months; 6-12 Months;     12-18 Months; 18-24 Months; 2T; 3T; 4T; 5T; S; M; L; XL

shoeStyle.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Flats; Pumps; Wedges; Comfort; Fashion; Heels; Steel Toe;     Walking; Running; WorkBoots; Slip-ons

shoeClosure.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Buckle; Single-Pull Lace; Hook-and-Loop; Zip-Up; Lace-Up; Pull-On;     Snap; Ankle Strap

mattressFirmness.fruugo_attribute_doc: The mattresses level of firmness.     Example: Ultra Plush; Plush; Medium; Firm; Extra Firm

isBabyFormulaLabelRequired.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates if item requires special nutrient labeling for baby formula.     Example: Y; N

babyFormulaLabel.fruugo_attribute_doc: URL of the location of the label. URLs must begin with http:// or https://   Nutrient information must contain the number of fluid ounces supplying 100 calories, a statement of the amount    of each of the nutrients listed, and any other nutrient added by the manufacturer, as supplied by 100 calories.     Example: http://www.example.com/formula_nutrients.html

isChildrenUnder2LabelRequired.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates if item requires special nutrient labeling for food for children     under 2 years old. Example: Y; N

childrenUnder2Label.fruugo_attribute_doc: URL of the location of the label. URLs must begin with http:// or https://      Foods, other than infant formula, represented or purported to be specifically for infants and children less than 2 years of age, must contain:    - Nutrient names and quantitative amounts by weight are presented in two separate columns   - The 'Percent Daily Value' heading is placed immediately below the quantitative information by weight for protein   - Percent daily value for protein, vitamins, and minerals are listed immediately below the 'Percent Daily Value' heading      The label must NOT contain:      - The '2000 Calorie Diet' footnote   - Calories from fat   - Calories from saturated fat   - Polyunsaturated fat   - Monounsaturated fat   - Cholesterol Example: http://www.example.com/food_under_4_nutrients.html

isChildrenUnder4LabelRequired.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates if item requires special nutrient labeling for food for children under 4 years old. Example: Y; N

childrenUnder4Label.fruugo_attribute_doc: URL of the location of the label. URLs must begin with http:// or https://      Nutrient information must contain:    - Nutrient names and quantitative amounts by weight are presented in two separate columns   - The 'Percent Daily Value' heading is placed immediately below the quantitative information by weight for protein   - Percent daily value for protein, vitamins, and minerals are listed immediately below the 'Percent Daily Value' heading   - The '2000 Calorie Diet' footnote is NOT included Example: http://www.example.com/food_under_2_nutrients.html

calories.fruugo_attribute_doc: Number of calories contained in one serving.

isFairTrade.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that the item is certified to be fairly traded.     Example: Y; N

metal.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Brass; Copper; Gold-Plated; Goldtone; Platinaire; Platinum; Rhodium;     Rose Gold; Silver-Plated; Silvertone; Stainless Steel; Sterling Silver; Titanium; Tungsten;     White Gold; Yellow Gold

isBulk.fruugo_attribute_doc: Intended for weighable or variably 'sized' items where Vendor Pack     Quantity (an integer value) is not all that helpful, for things like Fabric or Roving. Example: Y; N

isCollectible.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates if the item is regarded as being of value or interest           to a collector.

seatMaterial.fruugo_attribute_doc: The seat material if different than the item's main material makeup,           which is described using the 'Material' attribute. Example: Wood; Leather; Upholstered; Wicker

bedStyle.fruugo_attribute_doc: Describes the bed's shape and appearance according to thematic style or design   features. Example: Platform Bed; Storage Bed; Standard Bed; Classic Bed; Day Bed; Bookcase Bed;   Panel Bed; Sleigh Bed; Slat Bed; Metal Bed; Canopy Bed; Captain Bed; Four-Poster Bed; Novelty Bed;   Bunk Bed; Folding Bed; Trundle Bed

pumpIncluded.fruugo_attribute_doc: Is a pump included with the mattress? Example: Y; N

resolution.fruugo_attribute_doc: The commonly used resolution category of best fit for the panel.     1080p for a native resolution of 1920 x 1080, 4K for a native resolution of 4096 x 2160, and so on.      Example: 1080p (HDTV)

modelName.fruugo_attribute_doc: The model name of the product as commonly used in marketing communications.

hasBluetooth.fruugo_attribute_doc: Does the item provide wireless communication compatibility with     the Bluetooth standard? Example: Y; N

cellularNetworkTechnology.fruugo_attribute_doc: The cellular technology used by the device. Example: CDMA; GSM

hasFlash.fruugo_attribute_doc: Does the device incorporate a camera flash? Example: Y; N

hasTouchscreen.fruugo_attribute_doc: Does the display have touchscreen capabilities? Example: Y; N

backlightType.fruugo_attribute_doc: The backlighting used in the panel. Most commonly     Cold Cathode Fluorescent Lamps (CCFLs) or Light Emitting Diodes (LED's). Example: CCFL; LED

aspectRatio.fruugo_attribute_doc: The proportional relationship between the display's width and its height.   Commonly expressed as two numbers separated by a colon. Example: 4:3; 16:9; 21:9

nativeResolution.fruugo_attribute_doc: The resolution of a flat panel display at which no scaling is used to create     the images. This is the resolution that will render the highest picture quality when used with source     material of a corresponding resolution. Example: 2560 x 1080; 1920 x 1080; 4096 x 2160.

maximumContrastRatio.fruugo_attribute_doc: The ratio between the luminance of the brightest color to that of the darkest     color capable of being displayed. Example: 20,000:1; 30,000,000:1

hasIntegratedSpeakers.fruugo_attribute_doc: Does the item include speakers integrated into the body of the main item?     Example: Y; N

connectorFinish.fruugo_attribute_doc: The plating used on the electrical mating surfaces of the connectors.     Example: Gold; Tin

numberOfTwistedPairsPerCable.fruugo_attribute_doc: The number of twisted pair wires used within the cable. Example: 4; 100

hasAutomaticDocumentFeeder.fruugo_attribute_doc: Does the imaging device incorporate an automatic document feeder? Example: Y; N

hasAutomaticTwoSidedPrinting.fruugo_attribute_doc: Is the imaging device capable of providing two-sided prints automatically?     Example: Y; N

colorPagesPerMinute.fruugo_attribute_doc: The number of color pages that the imaging device is able to produce per minute.     Example: 12; 23

maximumDocumentSize.fruugo_attribute_doc: The maximum document size that the imaging device is capable of handling.     Example: Letter; A0

monochromeColor.fruugo_attribute_doc: Is the imaging device capable of color processing or monochrome only?     Example: Monochrome; Color

printingTechnology.fruugo_attribute_doc: The primary technology used to produce prints. Example: Laser; Inkjet; N/A

monochromePagesPerMinute.fruugo_attribute_doc: The number of monochrome pages that the imaging device is able to     produce per minute. Example: 50; 36

videoGameGenre.fruugo_attribute_doc: The game genre most strongly associated with the item.     Example: Fighting  Shooting; Simulation; Strategy  Role-Playing; Health  Fitness; Music  Poetry; Casual       Flight; Kids  Family; Sports  Racing; Cards  Puzzles; Action  Adventure

isOnlineMultiplayerAvailable.fruugo_attribute_doc: Does the game provide an online multiplayer option? Example: Y; N

isDownloadableContentAvailable.fruugo_attribute_doc: Is extra content available to extend or enhance gameplay via a download?     Example: Y; N

edition.fruugo_attribute_doc: The specific edition of the item.     Example: Game of the Year; Limited; Ghost; Black; Anniversary

videoGameCollection.fruugo_attribute_doc: The series of video game titles of which this is a part.     Example: Fallout; Grand Theft Auto; Call of Duty; Halo

requiredPeripherals.fruugo_attribute_doc: Any ancillary devices necessary to use the software.     Example: PlayStation Move; Kinect; Flatbed Scanner

version.fruugo_attribute_doc: The version number assigned to this specific release of the software.     Example: 7.2; 10.1

numberOfUsers.fruugo_attribute_doc: The maximum number of users or installations allowable under the     terms of the software licensing agreement. Example: 1; 15

softwareFormat.fruugo_attribute_doc: The format by which the software will be delivered, either through a     download or upon physical media such as optical disks (CD, BD-ROM], memory cards, floppy disks, etc.     Example: CD; DVD; Download

internalExternal.fruugo_attribute_doc: Primarily used to describe various drives, including hard drives.     Also applicable to a number of other items that may be designed for internal installation or may be      designed for external use (sound cards, memory card readers, network adapters, etc.)      Example: Internal; External

hasFrontFacingCamera.fruugo_attribute_doc: Does the item incorporate a front-facing camera? Example: Y; N

graphicsInformation.fruugo_attribute_doc: Basic graphics processor or graphics card information. Example: AMD Radeon HD 6410D; Nvidia GTX 8600

opticalDrive.fruugo_attribute_doc: Technology of the optical disk drive if one be present. Example: CD ROM. CD RW; BD ROM

formFactor.fruugo_attribute_doc: Commonly used term for the physical size to which the computer conforms. Example: Tower; Micro Tower; Nettop

throwRatio.fruugo_attribute_doc: A projector's throw ratio is defined as the distance (D], measured from lens to     screen, that a projector is placed from the screen, divided by the width (W) of the image that it will      project (D/W). Example: 1.8:1; 2.0:1

has3dCapabilities.fruugo_attribute_doc: Is the display capable of displaying 3D imagery when presented with the   appropriate source material? Example: Y; N

hasSignalBooster.fruugo_attribute_doc: Denotes if any portion of the item has a signal booster.   This information will be displayed on the item page. Example: Y; N

hasWirelessMicrophone.fruugo_attribute_doc: Denotes if any portion of the item has a wireless microphone.   This information will be displayed on the item page. Example: Y; N

audioPowerOutput.fruugo_attribute_doc: The audio output power of the amplifier or self-powered device's speakers,   expressed in Watts. A self-powered item has an internal amplifier; it does not need to be plugged into a    power amplifier to produce sound. Example: 5W + 5W; 7.5W

platform.fruugo_attribute_doc: The hardware upon which the video game is designed to run or with which the     product is compatible. Example: Mac; Nintendo DS  DSi; Nintendo 2DS; PlayStation 3; Nintendo Wii U;     Playstation Portable; PC; Playstation 4; Nintendo Wii; VTech InnoTab; Xbox 360; Nintendo 3DS;      Playstation 2; Xbox One

numberOfBurners.fruugo_attribute_doc: Number of burners on a cooktop Example: 2; 4

hasSideShelf.fruugo_attribute_doc: Whether grill has a utility shelf on the side of the main unit Example: Y; N

hasCharcoalBasket.fruugo_attribute_doc: Whether grill has a charcoal basket Example: Y; N

hasTankTray.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicator of whether a grill ha a tank tray Example: Y; N

digitalVideoFormats.fruugo_attribute_doc: The form in which the work is sold to the customer Example: DVD; Blu-Ray

tvShowGenre.fruugo_attribute_doc: The general category for the television show.     Example: Comedy; Drama; Documentary  Educational; Animation  Cartoons; Holidays; Special Interest;      Game Shows; TAlk  Variety Shows; Reality TV;

tvShowSubgenre.fruugo_attribute_doc: The more specific subcategory for the television show.     Example: British Comedy; Crime Drama; Sketch Comedy; Historical Documentary; Soap Opera

tvNetwork.fruugo_attribute_doc: The broadcast, cable, or online network which distributes the television program.     Example: Fox; CBS; NBC; HBO; PBS; Netflix

tvShowSeason.fruugo_attribute_doc: The set of television episodes recorded for the season of the calendar year,     usually airing from September until May. Example: 2; 7

numberOfEpisodes.fruugo_attribute_doc: The number of television episodes contained in the item. Example: 13; 26

episode.fruugo_attribute_doc: If the item is only one episode, the number of the episode. Example: 2; 321

director.fruugo_attribute_doc: Person who receives 'Directed by' billing on a film or television show.     Example: Joss Whedon; Kathryn Bigelow; Woody Allen; Penny Marshall

screenwriter.fruugo_attribute_doc: Person who is credited or billed as the primary writer on a film or television project. Example: John Hughes; Nora Ephron; Joel Coen; Tina Fey

studioProductionCompany.fruugo_attribute_doc: Company that is credited with creation of a film or television show.     Example: 20th Century Fox; Lionsgate; Dreamworks; NBC; HBO

videoStreamingQuality.fruugo_attribute_doc: The video resolution quality while streaming.     Example: Standard Definition; High Definition; Full High Definition

audioTrackCodec.fruugo_attribute_doc: The compression format or codec for the audio track.     Example: Dolby Digital 5.1; Dolby TrueHD; DTS; Dolby Pro Logic II

dvdReleaseDate.fruugo_attribute_doc: Date that the film or TV show was released on DVD. Example: 42005.0

isDubbed.fruugo_attribute_doc: A film or television show is dubbed if there is an audio track that replaces     the voices of the original actors with a different language Example: Y; N

hasSubtitles.fruugo_attribute_doc: A film or television show has subtitles if there is a transcript or     screenplay of the dialog or commentary displayed on the screen. Example: Y; N

seriesTitle.fruugo_attribute_doc: If the work is one of multiple works in a series, the title of the     series or collection. Example: The Millenium Trilogy; The Hunger Games Trilogy; Hooked on Classics

numberInSeries.fruugo_attribute_doc: The number in the series, if the work is one of multiple works in a series.     Example: 2; 4; 7

musicGenre.fruugo_attribute_doc: General music category.     Example: Karaoke; Christian  Gospel; World; Pop; New Age; Dance  DJ; Blues; Classical; Jazz; Holiday;     Reggae; Rock; Rap  Hip-Hop; Soundtracks; Latin; Comedy  Spoken Word; RB; Easy Listening; Country;      Children's; Folk

musicSubGenre.fruugo_attribute_doc: Specific music category.   Example: Motown; Salvadoran; Rumba; Chamber Music; Funk; Honky Tonk; Dub; Dixieland Jazz; Tejano;    Speed Metal; Celtic; Christmas; Film Soundtrack;

songwriter.fruugo_attribute_doc: A person credited with authorship of tracks on a music product   Example: James Taylor; Dolly Parton; Freddie Mercury

musicMediaFormat.fruugo_attribute_doc: The physical or digital format of the item. Example: CD; MP3; LP;

musicProducer.fruugo_attribute_doc: Person or entity credited with producing the album or single.   Example: Babyface; Brian Eno; T Bone Burnett; quincy Jones

recordLabel.fruugo_attribute_doc: The brand or publishing company associated with the item.   Example: Universal Music Group; Sony Music Entertainment; Warner Music Group

numberOfDiscs.fruugo_attribute_doc: Number of discs included in the item. Example: 2; 4

numberOfTracks.fruugo_attribute_doc: Number of tracks included in the item. Example: 13; 10

releaseDate.fruugo_attribute_doc: The date an item was released, for use especially with aged products, such as cheese. Example: 42005.0

musicReleaseType.fruugo_attribute_doc: A distinguishing feature of the release, such as number of tracks or type of performance. Example: Single, Extended Play, Recorded Live, Karaoke Version

hasParentalAdvisoryLabel.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates whether a music album has been labeled with a Parental Advisory label by the Recording Industry Association of America. Example: Y; N

bookFormat.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Paperback; Hardcover; eBook; Audiobook; Board Book

genre.fruugo_attribute_doc: The general book or magazine category. Example: Children's Books;   Literature  Fiction; Textbooks; Art, Music, and Photography; History; Home, Hobbies,  Garden; Health,   Mind  Body; Religion; Business  Investing; Political  Social Sciences; Romance; Biography  Memoirs;    Bibles; Comics  Graphic Novels; Computing  Internet; Cooking, Food  Wine; Mystery  Suspense; Parenting     Families; Sports  Recreation; Travel  Nature

subgenre.fruugo_attribute_doc: The more specific book or magazine subcategory.     Example: Cozy Mysteries; Crime Procedurals; Dystopian Science Fiction; Fashion; Gardening;      Popular Psychology; Italian Cooking; Cycling;

editor.fruugo_attribute_doc: The person or entity responsible for choosing the collection of stories or     articles in a book or magazine, as printed on the title page, or a magazine masthead Example: Anna     Wintour;

illustrator.fruugo_attribute_doc: The person credited with drawing illustrations within a printed work     Example: Hayao Miyazaki; Maurice Sendak

publisher.fruugo_attribute_doc: Publishing company as printed or displayed on the cover or title page.     Example: Brown and Co.; Pearson P T R; W.B. Saunders Company

translator.fruugo_attribute_doc: The person credited with translating the book from the original     language into the language of the current edition. Example: Dorothy L. Sayers; Jorge Luis Borges

translatedFrom.fruugo_attribute_doc: The original language that a work was translated from.     Example: Czech; Russian; French; Vietnamese

isUnabridged.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that the item is the complete original work with no omissions.     Example: Y; N

originalPublicationDate.fruugo_attribute_doc: Date that a printed work was first published, if different from the     publication date of the current edition. Example: 42005.0

publicationDate.fruugo_attribute_doc: Date of publication for the current edition. Example: 42005.0

readingLevel.fruugo_attribute_doc: The intended age or grade-level for a printed work.     Example: Young Adult; Ages 6-8; 3rd Grade

numberOfPages.fruugo_attribute_doc: Number of pages within a printed work. Example: 357.0

issue.fruugo_attribute_doc: For an ongoing serial publication, the specific issue, as named by the     publication, usually either month and year, or issue and volume number. Example: May 2015; Issue 4 Volume 7

movieGenre.fruugo_attribute_doc: General film category. Example: Romance; Documentary; Comedy; Kids  Family

movieSubgenre.fruugo_attribute_doc: More specific film subcategory. Example: Romantic Drama; Sports Documentary;     Stand-Up Comedy; Superheroes

theatricalReleaseDate.fruugo_attribute_doc: Date that a film was originally released in theaters. Example: 42005.0

title.fruugo_attribute_doc: The name given to the work. Does not include any marketing adjectives     outside of the given name. Example: Great Expectations; Seinfeld; Star Wars Episode IV- A New Hope;     Vogue; Thriller

numberOfSheets.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates the number of paper sheets in items, like pads of paper.     Also the number of sheets an office instrument can hold, such as paper punches or paper trays.

equalizerControl.fruugo_attribute_doc: Audio equalization features. Example: Bass; Mid; Treble; Parametric

musicalInstrumentFamily.fruugo_attribute_doc: The musical instrument family.     Example: Woodwind; Strings; Keyboards; Percussion; Brass

hardOrSoftCase.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates whether a case is a hard or soft.     Example: Hard; Soft

isTravelSize.fruugo_attribute_doc: Please indicate whether the product is a smaller version of a     larger-sized product. Example: Y; N

alcoholProof.fruugo_attribute_doc: Measure of ethanol (alcohol], which is twice the Alcohol by Volume. Example: 80 Proof

alcoholClassAndType.fruugo_attribute_doc: Designation of the alcohol class and type, as based on trade understanding its characteristics. Example: Malt Beverage; Lager; India Pale Ale; Stout; Pils; Pilsner; Whiskey; Scotch; Kentucky Straight Bourbon Whiskey; Gin; Rum; Spiced Rum

neutralSpiritsColoringAndFlavoring.fruugo_attribute_doc: A statement of composition, if an alcoholic beverage has additives. Example: Rum with natural flavors; Vodka with natural flavors; Grape wine with whey neutral spirits, natural flavors, and caramel color

whiskeyPercentage.fruugo_attribute_doc: In the case of a blended whiskey, percentage of whiskey or malt type. Example: 8% Straight Whiskey

isEstateBottled.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that 100% of the wine came from grapes grown on land owned or controlled by the winery, which must be located in a viticultural area. Example: Y; N

wineAppellation.fruugo_attribute_doc: Legally defined and public geographical indication used to identify where the grapes for a wine were grown. Example: CÃ´tes du RhÃ´ne; Champagne; Napa Valley; Alexander Valley

wineVarietal.fruugo_attribute_doc: Grape variety that wine is derived from or, in the absence of one varietal, the varietal blend. Example: Bordeaux; Rioja; Cabernet Sauvignon; Malbec; Chardonnay; Red Blend; Chablis; Rose

containsSulfites.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates if a beverage contains sulfites. Example: Y; N

isNonGrape.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that wine was made from fruit other than grapes. Example: Y; N

isNutritionFactsLabelRequired.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates if item requires nutritional facts labeling per FDA guidelines. Example: Y; N

nutritionFactsLabel.fruugo_attribute_doc: Image URL of the nutritional facts label. Example: http://www.example.com/nutrients.html

isImitation.fruugo_attribute_doc: Generally a new food that resembles a traditional food and is a substitute for the traditional food must be labeled as an imitation, if the new food contains less protein or a lesser amount of any essential vitamin or mineral. Example: Y; N

usdaInspected.fruugo_attribute_doc: Food products that are under the jurisdiction of the FSIS, and thus subject to inspection, are those that contain more than 3% meat or 2% poultry products, with several exceptions, and egg products (liquid, frozen or dried). See FDA for exceptions. Example: Y; N

vintage.fruugo_attribute_doc: The year the item was created, such as for wine or cheese. Example: 2014.0

isGmoFree.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that the item is free from genetically modified ingredients. Example: Y; N

isBpaFree.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that the item is free from Bisphenol A (BPA). Example: Y; N

isPotentiallyHazardousFood.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that item is capable of spoiling, if not handled or stored correctly. Example: Y; N

isReadyToEat.fruugo_attribute_doc: SEE FDA Food Code 2009: Chapter 1-201.10 Definitions Example: Y; N

caffeineDesignation.fruugo_attribute_doc: Differentiates between items that have no naturally occurring caffeine, caffeine removed by processing, naturally caffeinated, or added caffeine. Example: Naturally Caffeinated; Caffeine Added; Naturally Decaffeinated; Decaffeinated

spiceLevel.fruugo_attribute_doc: Level of spice (i.e., 'hotness') in an item, if applicable.     Example: Mild; Medium; Hot; Insane; Thai Hot

isMadeInHomeKitchen.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates if the item was made for consumption in a home kitchen, as defined by the FDA. Example: Y; N

safeHandlingInstructions.fruugo_attribute_doc: Instructions for storage or preparation of potentially hazardous fresh food. Example: Cook to internal temperature of 165 degrees.

fatCaloriesPerGram.fruugo_attribute_doc: Fat calories per gram per serving.

carbohydrateCaloriesPerGram.fruugo_attribute_doc: Carbohydrate calories per gram per serving.

proteinCaloriesPerGram.fruugo_attribute_doc: Protein calories per gram per serving.

attachmentStyle.fruugo_attribute_doc: Example: Screw Mount; Snap-On; Suction Cup

casualAndDressShoeType.fruugo_attribute_doc: The formality or environment for a shoe Example: Casual Shoes; Dress Shoes; Work/Safety Shoes; Dance Shoes

isOrthopedic.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates footwear designed to ease or improve musculoskeletal function. Example: Y; N

bagStyle.fruugo_attribute_doc: The style of the bag, comprised of form and function     Example: Crossbody; Messenger; Shoulder Bag; Tote Bag; Clutch; Wristlet; Satchel; Hobo;

fastenerType.fruugo_attribute_doc: Type of closure. Example: Snap; Magnetic; Turn Lock; Tuck Lock

numberOfCompartments.fruugo_attribute_doc: Number of separate compartments (as opposed to pockets) that a bag has.     Example: 2; 4

dimensions.fruugo_attribute_doc: Appropriate dimensions for the product, from the consumer point of view.     Example: 32 in x 72 in x 42 in

isLined.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates if the item contains a material lining on the interior.     Example: Y; N

designer.fruugo_attribute_doc: Name of the designer.     Example: Tommy Hilfiger; Calvin Klein; Vera Wang; Coco Chanel

leatherGrade.fruugo_attribute_doc: Grade of leather used in the item.     Example: A; B; Top-Grain; Aniline; Corrected Grain

monogramLetter.fruugo_attribute_doc: If the item has a monogram, indicate the letter/s.     Example: A; EMC; G;

lockingMechanism.fruugo_attribute_doc: Type of mechanism that locks the item.     Example: Padlock  Key; Combination Lock; Trunk Lock; Case Locking Catch

karats.fruugo_attribute_doc: Masure of the purity of gold, pure gold being 24 Karats     Example: 12K; 24K

birthstone.fruugo_attribute_doc: Name of month and birthstone for a particular gemstone     Example: April- Diamond; August- Peridot; December-Tanzanite, Zircon, Turquoise; February- methyst;     January- Garnet; July- Ruby; June - Pearl, Alexandrite; March- Aquamarine; May- Emerald; November- Topaz,      Citrine; October- Tourmaline, Opal; September- Sapphire

character\/characterValue.fruugo_attribute_doc: A person or entity portrayed in print or visual media. A character might be a fictional personality or an actual living person.  Example: Dora the Explorer; SpongeBob SquarePants

occasion\/occasionValue.fruugo_attribute_doc: The particular target time, event, or holiday for the product Example: Halloween; Christmas; Wedding; Anniversary

organicCertifications\/organicCertificat.fruugo_attribute_doc: Indicates that the item is certified organic by designating the certifying agent. Example: EU Organic; Global Organic Textile Standard (GOTS); Oregon Tilth Certified Organic  (OTCO); California Certified Organic; Farmers (CCOF); USDA Organic; Ecocert;   Farm Verified Organic (FVO); OCIA-Certified Organic; QIA Organic;    Canadian Organic Standards (COS)

nutrients\/nutrient.fruugo_attribute_doc: Additional nutrients, not including total fat or total carbohydrates, which should be entered in 'Total Fat' and 'Total Carbohydrate' respectively.
